---
import Layout from '~/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Content from '~/components/widgets/Content.astro';

const title = `Error 404`;
---

<Layout metadata={{ title }}>
  <Content
    id="404"
    columns={3}
    items={[
      {
        icon: 'tabler:backhoe',
        callToAction: {
          target: '_blank',
          text: 'Refresh',
          href: '/404lvl2', // Replace with actual link
        },
      },
      {
        icon: 'simple-icons:ubereats',
        callToAction: {
          target: '_blank',
          text: 'home',
          href: '/',
        },
      },
    ]}
    image={{
      src: '~/assets/images/Notion 404.png',
      alt: '404',
      loading: '4-0-4',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white sm:text-3xl mb-2">⚠️ Oops!</h2>

      <p>
        It looks like this page didn’t make it into the current sprint. The roadmap shifted, priorities changed, and now
        we’re left with a 404. But don’t worry—our next iteration is on it!
      </p>
      <br />

      <p><strong>Possible Causes:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>The feature request (a.k.a. this page) wasn’t properly scoped.</li>
        <li>Stakeholders (you) are looking for something still in development.</li>
        <li>The roadmap changed, and this item got de-prioritized. 😅</li>
      </ul>
      <br />

      <p><strong>Next Steps:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Check the homepage for available features.</li>
        <li>Contact the product owner (me) for updates.</li>
        <li>Refresh and hope for an A/B test miracle. 🤞</li>
      </ul>
    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="bg">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-transparent"></div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>
</Layout>
